1
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:09,259
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

2
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,226
-Hello?
-Hi.

3
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:20,437
Mom said I'm supposed to remind you
to pick her up for lunch.

4
00:00:20,646 --> 00:00:22,231
Was I supposed to have lunch with her?

5
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>She said she left you five messages.</i>

6
00:00:24,942 --> 00:00:27,444
Bite the bullet
and have a Cobb salad with the woman.

7
00:00:27,653 --> 00:00:30,864
Sometimes it's difficult to remember
which one of you is my mother.

8
00:00:31,782 --> 00:00:36,119
Mrs. Queen, all I'm asking for is a chance
to sit down and discuss our proposal.

9
00:00:36,328 --> 00:00:39,039
If that's all it is,
then I can save us both the time.

10
00:00:39,248 --> 00:00:41,124
-It's rejected.
-I see. May I ask why?

11
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,460
Do I really need to answer that,
Mr. Copani?

12
00:00:45,087 --> 00:00:48,257
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'm meeting my son for lunch.

13
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:53,720
[TIRES SCREECH]

14
00:01:01,353 --> 00:01:02,646
Get down!

15
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:06,650
[EXHALES]

16
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:10,654
-Mom? Are you okay?
-I'm all right.

17
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:12,072
-Are you hurt?
-No, I'm...

18
00:01:12,281 --> 00:01:14,032
-Are you sure?
-I'm fine. I'm fine.

19
00:01:14,241 --> 00:01:16,118
Call 911.

20
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:27,170
[CAR TIRES SCREECH]

21
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:48,358
[HORN HONKS]

22
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:52,070
[PANTING]

23
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:07,669
Hi.

24
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:10,047
-Are you okay?
-I'm fine.

25
00:02:11,006 --> 00:02:13,133
I'm fine.

26
00:02:13,884 --> 00:02:16,845
-Did you reach Walter?
-No, I'm sorry.

27
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:19,222
As I was telling
your mother and sister...

28
00:02:19,431 --> 00:02:23,185
...the CAT scan showed a grade-2
concussion. She can go home so long...

29
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:26,188
...as someone stays with her.

30
00:02:26,396 --> 00:02:28,065
-Thank you.
MOIRA: Hm.

31
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:32,611
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have left you.
I thought you were fine.

32
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,571
What did you think you were doing?

33
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:38,033
I wanted to get the license plate
of the guy who took a shot at you.

34
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:41,244
-Well, that was foolish.
-Yeah.

35
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:52,839
-So did you get the license plate?
-No, he got away.

36
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:56,009
Maybe you should spend
a little less time trying to be a hero.

37
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:58,470
You're obviously not very good at it.

38
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:00,472
-That's cute.
-Wasn't trying to be.

39
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:05,769
You left Mom in the street.
Alone and hurt in the street.

40
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,814
Heh, to get a license plate?

41
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:19,866
-You don't believe me?
-I love you. Mom loves you.

42
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:23,995
But it's getting hard
when you won't be truthful with us.

43
00:03:33,212 --> 00:03:34,464
Detectives.

44
00:03:34,673 --> 00:03:37,008
-Do you have any leads on the shooter?
-Not yet.

45
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,678
-Did you get a look at him?
-He was wearing a helmet.

46
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,681
-Don't worry. We'll find him.
-My head of security is on his way.

47
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:45,058
I wanna make sure there are men
outside my mother's door.

48
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,643
She needs to be protected.

49
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:49,938
You know your family's
at the tippy-top of my list of priorities.

50
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,773
The guy she was with was connected.

51
00:03:51,982 --> 00:03:56,069
Mobbed-up-to-the-eyeballs connected.
She wasn't the target.

52
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,366
And you're welcome.

53
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:06,329
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

54
00:04:10,459 --> 00:04:14,296
Uh, technically, I did get here, like,
10 seconds before this guy.

55
00:04:17,174 --> 00:04:18,216
Keep the change.

56
00:04:20,552 --> 00:04:23,221
So, Tommy,
what brings you by so late?

57
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:26,725
Well, I assumed, rightly, that you would
be at home working tonight...

58
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:30,645
...and I also assumed
that you might be hungry. Also rightly.

59
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:32,522
I don't know.

60
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:35,484
This is a mushroom and olive pizza
from Mario's.

61
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:37,861
Oh, that is damn good pie.

62
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:43,658
-All right. What do you have to offer?
-Spicy tuna on crispy rice from Toro.

63
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,285
Oh.

64
00:04:45,494 --> 00:04:49,039
Damn you, Merlyn.
I hope sushi was all you had in mind.

65
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:53,084
Uh, actually, there was something
that I wanted to ask you.

66
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:56,505
-And what's that?
-Will you go out with me?

67
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:58,757
Like, on a date?

68
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:01,218
You brought me dinner
to ask me to dinner?

69
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:04,513
Oh, uh, well, I also did throw you
a really big charity gala.

70
00:05:04,721 --> 00:05:08,266
See, I thought you threw it for
the hundreds of people it would benefit.

71
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:11,895
Oh, yeah, hundreds of people.
Plus one more.

72
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:13,647
-Tommy, heh.
-Laurel.

73
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:16,900
I get it. Okay, this is all happening
for us in the wrong order.

74
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:19,486
First, we're friends for many years...

75
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:22,989
...and then, briefly,
we are friends with benefits...

76
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:27,202
...extremely excellent benefits,
and now I'm just hoping...

77
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:30,372
...that we can be two people
sitting at the same restaurant...

78
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,874
...at the same table at the same time.

79
00:05:33,083 --> 00:05:36,545
See, when I say it like that,
it doesn't sound so scary, does it?

80
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,220
Oliver, your mom's nearly killed...

81
00:05:45,428 --> 00:05:48,098
...I think you can take a day off
from training.

82
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:50,767
My mother wasn't the target.

83
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:52,185
This man was. Paul Copani.

84
00:05:52,394 --> 00:05:55,438
He was trying to close a deal with her
when they were shot at.

85
00:05:55,647 --> 00:05:57,732
Copani works
for Bertinelli Construction.

86
00:05:57,941 --> 00:06:00,902
-And Frank Bertinelli.
-The mob boss.

87
00:06:01,111 --> 00:06:02,571
I did some digging.

88
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:05,907
Copani isn't the first member
of Bertinelli's crew who's been hit.

89
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:07,158
You did some digging.

90
00:06:07,366 --> 00:06:09,411
Bertinelli has a lot of enemies.

91
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:12,914
The best way to figure out
who's trying to target his organization...

92
00:06:13,123 --> 00:06:16,375
-...is to get inside of it.
-So let me get this right, Oliver.

93
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:20,463
Your mother's shot at, nearly killed, and
the way you process this emotionally...

94
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:24,968
-...is by going undercover with the mob.
-I'm not trying to process it emotionally.

95
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:27,971
Yeah, well,
maybe that's your problem, man.

96
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:31,766
You ever thought about
just being there for your family?

97
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:34,769
I tried that today with Thea.

98
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:37,814
She told me I wasn't being honest
with her and she's right.

99
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:41,610
I can't very well explain to her
that I left our mother alone...

100
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:44,779
...and bleeding on the pavement
because I'm fast enough...

101
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:47,282
...to almost run down the attacker.

102
00:06:49,868 --> 00:06:53,622
But what I can do
is protect my family.

103
00:06:55,081 --> 00:07:01,922
And, Diggle, when I find out
who this guy is, he's a dead man.

104
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:45,507
-Speedy, where you going?
-Clubbing.

105
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:48,802
Which is difficult to do in your house
and not at an actual club.

106
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,887
I have to go out tonight.

107
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:54,891
-I thought you'd be watching Mom.
-I've spent the whole day with her.

108
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:58,895
-I thought you were taking the night shift.
-I'm sorry, but this thing, it's important.

109
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:00,271
[SIGHS]

110
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,608
You know, sometimes, Ollie,
I just don't get you.

111
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,860
And by "sometimes" I mean never.

112
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:08,571
You're not the first person
to say that to me today.

113
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,407
Why am I not surprised?

114
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:15,745
-Oh, nice dress. Where you headed?
-Upstairs. Apparently.

115
00:08:16,788 --> 00:08:19,290
-Long story.
-Hey, I heard about your mom.

116
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,793
-Is she all right?
-Well, she's resting upstairs.

117
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:23,420
More shaken up than anything.

118
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:26,715
I gotta run to this, uh, business thing.
I appreciate you stopping by.

119
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:29,384
No problem.
Just so long as your mom's all right.

120
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:31,177
Yeah.

121
00:08:31,386 --> 00:08:33,763
Hey, one more thing.

122
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:38,226
Mainly because I don't want you
to find this out from someone else...

123
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:41,062
...that someone else
especially being Laurel...

124
00:08:41,271 --> 00:08:42,605
...uh...

125
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:46,776
...we're going to dinner,
as in a, uh, date.

126
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:49,362
That's good.

127
00:08:49,571 --> 00:08:52,699
Laurel deserves someone special
and so do you.

128
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:54,200
Thanks, man.

129
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:56,911
-I gotta run to this thing.
-Absolutely. I'll catch you later.

130
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:00,790
Oh, and, uh, Tommy, if you hurt her,
I'll snap your neck.

131
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,710
I'm just kidding, heh.

132
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,217
[DOORBELL RINGS]

133
00:09:14,763 --> 00:09:15,805
Mr. Bertinelli.

134
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:18,975
-Call me Frank.
-Call me Oliver.

135
00:09:19,184 --> 00:09:20,810
Yeah, heh.

136
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:23,605
Thank you for agreeing to meet me
at my home.

137
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:26,566
Living rooms make
the best conference rooms.

138
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:28,610
-Oh, I'm gonna steal that.
-Heh.

139
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:32,322
-Nick Salvati, my associate.
-How do you do?

140
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:34,449
Let's have a drink.

141
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,544
THEA:
So, what are you in the mood for, hmm?

142
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:52,759
We could watch reality housewife
cooking show or <i>Cop Docs.</i>

143
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,095
It's where doctors run around
fighting crime...

144
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:57,222
...when they're not all
sleeping with each other.

145
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:58,515
[CHUCKLES]

146
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,308
Whatever you want, sweetheart.

147
00:10:00,517 --> 00:10:02,477
You're the one who's given up
your evening out.

148
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:05,772
Aw, it's not like there's anybody else
who could be staying with you.

149
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,023
[GASPS]

150
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:10,485
-Oh, wait, yes, there is.
-Don't be too harsh on your brother.

151
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:12,028
[SCOFFS]

152
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:16,032
Why not? I mean,
aren't you getting, heh, sick of his lies?

153
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,912
Thea, everyone has secrets.

154
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:25,625
I mean, we all have things
that we wanna keep to ourselves.

155
00:10:28,211 --> 00:10:30,046
I just don't get him sometimes.

156
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:33,800
I know.

157
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,095
I know.

158
00:10:41,015 --> 00:10:44,435
You know, being in that hospital
and seeing Dr. Lamb again...

159
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:48,231
...it made me remember the day
that Oliver came home.

160
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,611
It was Dr. Lamb that told me
that the Oliver we'd lost...

161
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:56,239
...might not be the Oliver
that they'd found.

162
00:10:56,447 --> 00:11:02,787
I think it's easy to forget, but he lived
apart from civilization for 5 years.

163
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:04,038
THEA:
Hm.

164
00:11:04,247 --> 00:11:10,211
-So, what, he gets, like, a free pass?
-No, no, no, not at all.

165
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:14,841
I just think we need to stop judging him
for the Oliver he was...

166
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:19,262
...and start accepting him
for the Oliver that he is.

167
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:26,436
So, Oliver, I'll be honest with you,
I was surprised to hear from you.

168
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,313
It was my impression from the news...

169
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,107
...that you weren't gonna be involved
with your family's business.

170
00:11:31,316 --> 00:11:34,444
There were a few catchphrases I missed
while I was away for five years.

171
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:36,321
One of them being
lame-stream media.

172
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:37,864
[ALL CHUCKLE]

173
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:41,075
-The press never gets anything right.
-Oh, I know a thing or two about that.

174
00:11:41,284 --> 00:11:42,660
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

175
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,913
-So, Oliver, I'll be blunt.
-Hmm?

176
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:46,206
I want the contract...

177
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:49,167
...to build Queen Consolidated's
new applied sciences division.

178
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:53,254
-And I'm inclined to give it to you.
-Your mother wasn't so enthusiastic.

179
00:11:54,005 --> 00:11:57,926
-How is she by the way?
-She's recuperating at home, thank you.

180
00:11:58,134 --> 00:11:59,385
What a terrible thing.

181
00:11:59,594 --> 00:12:04,057
And, Frank, I was very sorry to hear
about what happened to Paul Copani.

182
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:08,394
Paul was a good friend.
He was a good man.

183
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:09,812
[SIGHS]

184
00:12:10,021 --> 00:12:11,481
The violence in this city...

185
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:13,233
Sometimes I wonder why I stay.

186
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:15,818
I had the same thought.

187
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:18,488
So why'd you come back?

188
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:21,199
You could have settled
anywhere in the world.

189
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:23,117
Because Starling City is my home.

190
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:26,162
[SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

191
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:32,377
No matter which way you go or turn,
you always end up at home.

192
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:37,382
-Oliver, this is my daughter, Helena.
-Hello.

193
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:42,971
-Nice to meet you. I'm heading out.
-All right. Take one of the guys with you.

194
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,181
-I can take care of myself.
-Heh.

195
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,476
I wasn't asking, sweetie.

196
00:12:48,685 --> 00:12:52,981
Frank, that meeting you requested?
They can do it.

197
00:12:53,648 --> 00:12:54,691
Now.

198
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:01,906
-I can come back another time.
-No, no, no. Just, uh...

199
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:05,451
Just excuse us for a moment,
would you?

200
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:07,578
OLIVER: Mm-hm.
-Thank you.

201
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:14,377
Oliver Queen.
The rich man's Lindsay Lohan.

202
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:16,879
Look, um...

203
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:20,300
...I've gotta go to this other meeting.

204
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:22,427
But I need someone
to take him to dinner.

205
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:24,053
So you pimp out your daughter.

206
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:27,015
No, I ask her to help me
close a business deal.

207
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:30,268
I remind her
that the family business is dying...

208
00:13:30,476 --> 00:13:33,771
...and that we need this contract
and Oliver Queen can give it to us.

209
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:38,067
Please, sweet pea, huh?
For us. For me, hmm?

210
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,029
That's my girl.

211
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:44,741
Oliver, I'm so sorry,
something has come up.

212
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:48,411
But Helena would love to take you
to dinner and discuss the deal further.

213
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:49,828
-Oh.
HELENA: Hm.

214
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:51,497
I was hoping to speak with you.

215
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:56,377
Well, as you, uh, speak for your family,
my daughter also speaks for ours.

216
00:13:57,086 --> 00:14:00,381
It's really not necessary.

217
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:04,761
-It'd be my pleasure.
-Sure.

218
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,181
I look forward to working together.

219
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:32,246
FRANK: Thank you for coming.
-Anything for a friend.

220
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:35,249
[SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

221
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:41,381
We're not responsible
for the attacks on your people.

222
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:48,429
These attacks on my business,
on my family's lifeblood, they stop now.

223
00:14:48,638 --> 00:14:49,764
Or I'm coming for you.

224
00:14:56,771 --> 00:14:57,855
[SIGHS]

225
00:14:58,064 --> 00:15:01,275
What does the Triad have to gain
by provoking you?

226
00:15:01,484 --> 00:15:05,822
Well, no one ever credited the Triad
with rational thinking.

227
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:09,951
If not them, then who?

228
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:11,619
FRANK [OVER COMPUTER]:
<i>Whoever it is...</i>

229
00:15:11,828 --> 00:15:14,038
<i>...when I find out who's behind this,
there will be blood.</i>

230
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:16,499
Bertinelli's ready to put the screws
to everyone...

231
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:18,292
...who pays him protection money.

232
00:15:18,501 --> 00:15:20,837
Three of his best earners
have been murdered.

233
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:22,880
He's gotta make up the cash
somewhere.

234
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:27,677
Whoever is pruning the family tree
is looking to make Bertinelli suffer.

235
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:30,430
-You think it's one of the other families?
-No.

236
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:31,764
HILTON:
Then who?

237
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:34,851
According to the coroner,
none of the vics took a clean shot.

238
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:37,728
Half the bullets missed.
Our killer is not a pro.

239
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:40,356
That's not stopping them
from pulling that trigger.

240
00:15:40,565 --> 00:15:42,024
That's up to us.

241
00:15:43,568 --> 00:15:46,070
Or this is gonna blow up
into an all-out mob war.

242
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:57,623
-You're an angel, Helena. So beautiful.
-Heh.

243
00:15:58,249 --> 00:16:01,669
Well, we are gonna take good care
of both of you tonight.

244
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:06,424
-You'll tell your father hello from us?
-Of course, Mr. Russo.

245
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:08,384
-I'll give you a minute.
-Thank you.

246
00:16:11,846 --> 00:16:13,890
I heard about your mother's accident.

247
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:17,310
-Is she gonna be okay?
-She's gonna be fine. Thanks.

248
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:20,188
I'm glad.

249
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:27,487
So why would you wanna go
into business with my father?

250
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,490
You know who he is
and how he made his money.

251
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:32,909
You don't approve
of your family's enterprises?

252
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,285
We share a name.

253
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:37,580
That name defines us
whether we want it to or not.

254
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:39,874
You've already made judgments
about me...

255
00:16:40,082 --> 00:16:41,959
...like I've made judgments about you.

256
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:44,879
Right.
I'm the rich man's Lindsay Lohan.

257
00:16:45,421 --> 00:16:47,632
Heh, sorry.

258
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:50,259
-That's okay.
-Heh.

259
00:16:53,346 --> 00:16:56,557
-Hey, can I ask you something?
-Yeah.

260
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:59,393
I know it must have been hell for you...

261
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:02,855
...alone on that island for five years,
but, um...

262
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:05,733
But what?

263
00:17:07,235 --> 00:17:12,907
But was there ever a day when you were
just happy to be away from everything?

264
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:14,951
No pressure from your family.

265
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:18,496
No need to be the person
that everyone else expects you to be.

266
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:23,167
-Was there ever a day when...?
-When I didn't feel lost, that I felt...

267
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:24,502
...free?

268
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:27,838
[CHUCKLES]

269
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:30,925
More than one and, uh...

270
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:34,929
And those are the days that I miss.

271
00:17:39,976 --> 00:17:42,770
[TOMMY GASPS THEN COUGHS]

272
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:46,274
-What, is it too spicy for you, Merlyn?
-No. No, not really.

273
00:17:46,482 --> 00:17:50,611
I'm just, um, crying because I was thinking
of a Hallmark commercial...

274
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:53,614
...I saw earlier today
featuring a sick kitty.

275
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:55,575
It was very emotional.

276
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:57,285
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

277
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:00,705
WAITER: Will there be anything else?
-No, thank you.

278
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:02,456
Yep.

279
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:05,876
Thanks for letting me
take you to dinner.

280
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:08,754
Well, thank you
for letting me choose Indian.

281
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:14,969
Yeah, I read this article
by a film critic once who said...

282
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:19,682
...if he could have one wish it would be
to watch his favorite movie again...

283
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:21,392
...for the first time.

284
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:24,687
I kind of wish that was us.

285
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,481
So you want dinner and a movie?

286
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:29,692
No.

287
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:34,697
I wish we had just met,
and that all this was just beginning...

288
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:39,535
...and there wasn't so much of me
I wish you'd forget.

289
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:41,912
Well, keep saying nice things
like that...

290
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:44,915
...and maybe next time
I'll let you choose the restaurant.

291
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:49,378
-Mr. Merlyn?
-Yeah.

292
00:18:49,587 --> 00:18:52,256
I'm sorry, I'm afraid your credit card
has been declined.

293
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:55,593
You swipe it a few times?
Sometimes those things can be glitchy.

294
00:18:55,801 --> 00:19:00,723
I did. And, um, I'm afraid the credit card
company wants me to confiscate it.

295
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:04,018
Sorry.

296
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:09,482
OLIVER: People are always asking me
what did I miss the most.

297
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,400
[SIGHS]

298
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:16,572
Uh, air conditioning.
Satellite radio. Taglia...

299
00:19:16,781 --> 00:19:18,032
-Tagliatelle?
-Right.

300
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,283
Hmm.

301
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:23,245
Those are the answers I give because
those are the answers they're expecting.

302
00:19:23,454 --> 00:19:27,208
-Why can't you just be truthful?
-I don't know how truthful I can be.

303
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:32,505
You've been through a crucible.
And it changed you. How could it not?

304
00:19:35,383 --> 00:19:37,760
That's beautiful. Your cross.

305
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:45,017
-It's a gift. From my fiancé.
-Heh, fiancé.

306
00:19:45,226 --> 00:19:50,106
-I didn't know you were engaged.
-I'm not. Anymore.

307
00:19:51,232 --> 00:19:53,651
-He died.
-I'm sorry.

308
00:19:54,485 --> 00:19:56,237
Me too.

309
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:59,281
That was my crucible.

310
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:04,245
Boy, it's nice to...

311
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:08,082
It's really nice to be with someone
that I can be myself with.

312
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:11,001
It's nice to be with someone
who knows how hard it can be.

313
00:20:11,210 --> 00:20:12,253
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]

314
00:20:12,461 --> 00:20:14,797
-Ugh, I'm really sorry.
-It's okay. Take it.

315
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,549
Thank you.

316
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:18,759
-Yeah.
DIGGLE: <i>Hey, it's Dig.</i>

317
00:20:18,968 --> 00:20:20,010
<i>Something came up.</i>

318
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,680
<i>You gotta get out of there
and call me back.</i>

319
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:27,435
Helena, I have to go.
There's something that I have to do.

320
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:31,814
It's about my mother.
Otherwise, I would, uh, stay.

321
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:33,315
And I would like that.

322
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:40,406
Uh, my father would kill me
if I let you pay.

323
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:45,828
[SCOFFS]

324
00:20:47,496 --> 00:20:49,290
I have a confession.

325
00:20:51,417 --> 00:20:54,545
-I didn't wanna go out with you tonight.
-That makes two of us.

326
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:56,088
I'm really glad that I did.

327
00:20:56,672 --> 00:20:57,882
That makes two of us.

328
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,592
[CHUCKLES]

329
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,802
Oliver.

330
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:04,263
Be careful with my father.

331
00:21:11,812 --> 00:21:12,855
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

332
00:21:13,063 --> 00:21:14,690
Thea, you don't need to knock,
sweetheart.

333
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:15,941
[DOOR OPENS]

334
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:17,693
MAN:
What about me?

335
00:21:18,194 --> 00:21:19,236
I hope you don't mind.

336
00:21:20,488 --> 00:21:22,114
Thea let me in.

337
00:21:22,323 --> 00:21:23,449
What are you doing here?

338
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:25,493
I wanted to see how your recovery
was going.

339
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:27,828
Surely someone of your means
has a telephone.

340
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,457
I like to see someone when I have
something important to talk about.

341
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:35,711
We used to be friends, Moira.

342
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:40,174
I still remember that time.

343
00:21:40,382 --> 00:21:42,802
You, me and Robert.

344
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:46,096
Which is why I came by.

345
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:51,060
You are a vital part
of Starling City's future.

346
00:21:51,769 --> 00:21:54,146
Robert feared that future.

347
00:21:54,855 --> 00:21:57,191
He lost his conviction.

348
00:21:58,442 --> 00:22:02,196
It's been my experience that
when someone has a brush with death...

349
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:08,828
...like you experienced today, even their
deepest held convictions can change.

350
00:22:09,829 --> 00:22:13,457
-Have they?
-No.

351
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,168
You didn't have to say it.

352
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:21,131
I can see that they haven't.

353
00:22:27,805 --> 00:22:30,307
-What happened?
-Yeah, it's what's about to happen.

354
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:32,226
Bertinelli's enforcer, Nick Salvati?

355
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,938
Yeah, we drank a Scotch together,
he seems like a real stand-up mobster.

356
00:22:36,146 --> 00:22:39,233
He's paying visits to everyone
who owes the mob protection money.

357
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:42,069
I'm trying to figure out
who took a shot at my mother...

358
00:22:42,278 --> 00:22:44,071
...not take on all of organized crime.

359
00:22:44,280 --> 00:22:47,157
Salvati and his goons have put
four people in the hospital...

360
00:22:47,365 --> 00:22:49,201
...and if somebody doesn't stop him...

361
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:51,745
...the poor bastard
who owns Russo's is next.

362
00:22:51,954 --> 00:22:54,623
-Wait, wait. Russo's?
<i>-It's at the corner of Adams...</i>

363
00:22:54,832 --> 00:22:56,667
I know where it is. I'm here right now.

364
00:22:56,876 --> 00:22:58,376
What?

365
00:22:58,586 --> 00:23:00,796
I was having dinner
with Bertinelli's daughter.

366
00:23:01,005 --> 00:23:02,631
You're supposed to be undercover...

367
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:04,967
-...not speed dating.
-I didn't have a choice.

368
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:10,139
Yeah, well, uh, I've seen her on the web.
You made quite the sacrifice.

369
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:16,979
Salvati's here.

370
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:24,612
I'm sorry, we're closed.

371
00:23:27,281 --> 00:23:30,659
Huh? Mr. Salvati.

372
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:33,287
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

373
00:23:34,204 --> 00:23:38,416
-Uh, I have some fresh-made lasagna.
SALVATI: We're not here for food, Mr. Russo.

374
00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:42,671
-Your payment's due.
-I already made my payment this month.

375
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:44,882
You need to pay again.

376
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:47,301
I can't afford to make
another payment if I'm...

377
00:23:47,509 --> 00:23:51,096
Going to what? Restock your bar?

378
00:23:53,766 --> 00:23:56,477
-Break his fingers.
-Leave him alone!

379
00:23:56,685 --> 00:23:58,395
-Break hers too.
-No, don't touch her!

380
00:23:58,604 --> 00:24:00,689
[EXPLODES]

381
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:02,650
[MAN GRUNTS]

382
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:04,109
OLIVER:
Go!

383
00:24:04,442 --> 00:24:05,486
[GUNSHOTS]

384
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:18,874
[BOTH GRUNTING]

385
00:24:24,755 --> 00:24:26,131
[PANTING]

386
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:38,185
OLIVER:
I don't understand.

387
00:24:38,394 --> 00:24:40,729
-Why is she targeting her family?
-I don't know.

388
00:24:40,938 --> 00:24:44,274
-Here I thought you had parental issues.
-This is not a joke, Diggle.

389
00:24:44,482 --> 00:24:46,819
Oliver, you're not falling for this girl,
are you?

390
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:49,530
Because I know
you can't be that crazy.

391
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,532
Helena Bertinelli shot at your mother.

392
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,951
She also murdered four men
in cold blood.

393
00:24:54,159 --> 00:24:58,122
She has to have reasons
for what she's doing.

394
00:24:58,956 --> 00:25:00,791
Reasons?

395
00:25:01,499 --> 00:25:03,919
Since when do you care
about the bad guy's reasons?

396
00:25:04,128 --> 00:25:07,505
Oh, she is bad guy, Oliver.
She's the killer.

397
00:25:07,715 --> 00:25:10,092
Whatever's going on in your head,
get it straight.

398
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:12,678
Any attempt on his right hand...

399
00:25:12,886 --> 00:25:16,390
...is gonna send your new friend's father
on a warpath.

400
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:20,769
I know what I'm doing.

401
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:27,776
Now I know how your family feels
when you lie to them.

402
00:25:33,907 --> 00:25:35,533
Is this the only angle you've got?

403
00:25:35,743 --> 00:25:38,412
The Russos chintzed out a bit
on their security package.

404
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:41,373
Somebody's in the wings with a gun
shooting at these guys.

405
00:25:41,582 --> 00:25:44,542
-What do you got from earlier? Yeah.
-Before the shooting?

406
00:25:44,752 --> 00:25:47,421
Business dinner, birthday dinner,
couple of blind dates.

407
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:49,673
Any guests
of the Chinese persuasion?

408
00:25:49,882 --> 00:25:51,300
-Why?
-Humor me.

409
00:25:56,805 --> 00:25:58,015
Whoa, whoa.

410
00:25:58,223 --> 00:26:01,268
-Wait. Wait a second, what was that?
-Help yourself.

411
00:26:01,769 --> 00:26:03,062
Come on.

412
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:10,568
Son of a bitch.

413
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:13,822
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

414
00:26:17,868 --> 00:26:20,245
Detective. Is everything okay?

415
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:24,208
Your, um...

416
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:26,919
Your buddy with the arrows
was at Russo's last night.

417
00:26:27,127 --> 00:26:33,509
And I was there earlier with a date. So,
what, you think I'm the hood guy again?

418
00:26:34,218 --> 00:26:36,512
Heh, no.

419
00:26:37,179 --> 00:26:41,850
Your date. Helena Bertinelli.
If I were you, I'd stay away from her.

420
00:26:42,059 --> 00:26:44,144
Her family is bad news on a good day.

421
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:47,648
Why the sudden concern
for my well-being?

422
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:53,570
A few weeks ago, I made a mistake.

423
00:26:54,363 --> 00:26:55,864
I almost got you killed.

424
00:26:57,991 --> 00:26:59,660
And you felt like you owed me one?

425
00:27:00,452 --> 00:27:04,373
If I did, as far as I'm concerned,
this clears the books.

426
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:19,888
Can I talk to you? Dad.

427
00:27:20,097 --> 00:27:23,684
MALCOLM: In case you haven't noticed,
I'm a little occupied at the moment.

428
00:27:23,892 --> 00:27:26,979
I just talked to the accountant.
He said my accounts were frozen.

429
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:29,398
He said my credit cards
were all canceled.

430
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:33,026
MALCOLM: I pay Sandy a king's ransom
each year in fees, Tommy.

431
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:37,823
When it comes to money,
if he says it's so, it's so.

432
00:27:38,031 --> 00:27:40,325
Do you think this is a joke?

433
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:43,078
MALCOLM:
No.

434
00:27:43,287 --> 00:27:44,329
[PANTING]

435
00:27:44,538 --> 00:27:46,331
You are.

436
00:27:47,708 --> 00:27:50,460
Although, I must say,
your chronic irresponsibility...

437
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:54,214
...and terminal laziness
has lost its humor.

438
00:27:55,591 --> 00:27:56,633
Heh.

439
00:27:56,842 --> 00:27:58,343
You're wondering why now.

440
00:27:58,552 --> 00:28:03,182
-The better question is why not sooner?
-It's...

441
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:08,729
-It's my trust fund.
-Which is comprised of my money.

442
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:11,273
Oh, excuse me.

443
00:28:13,567 --> 00:28:16,195
Was comprised.

444
00:28:50,896 --> 00:28:51,939
Helena.

445
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:57,986
-How did you find me here?
-I followed you from your house.

446
00:28:59,238 --> 00:29:00,447
Your fiancé?

447
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:05,285
Yeah.

448
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:14,211
You said that losing him
was your crucible.

449
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:18,173
That it changed you.
You didn't say how.

450
00:29:22,803 --> 00:29:26,515
When you love someone
as much as I loved him...

451
00:29:26,723 --> 00:29:28,392
...with all of your heart...

452
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:33,313
...then you can't just turn that emotion
off when they're taken from you.

453
00:29:33,855 --> 00:29:37,359
You still feel things as deeply.
And if it...

454
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:40,320
If it can't be love that you feel...

455
00:29:42,406 --> 00:29:43,782
...then it becomes hate.

456
00:29:44,533 --> 00:29:45,909
Hate for who?

457
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:48,704
Oliver.

458
00:29:54,167 --> 00:29:56,003
You should stay away from me.

459
00:29:58,797 --> 00:29:59,840
Helena.

460
00:30:07,222 --> 00:30:08,849
Get in.

461
00:30:18,567 --> 00:30:21,528
My father is going to kill you for this.

462
00:30:21,737 --> 00:30:22,946
[CHUCKLES]

463
00:30:23,447 --> 00:30:25,198
[GRUNTS]

464
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:34,124
I've been wanting to do that for years,
you spoiled bitch.

465
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:39,629
I knew it was someone from the inside
waging war against your father and me.

466
00:30:39,838 --> 00:30:42,632
I just never thought it'd be this inside.

467
00:30:43,216 --> 00:30:44,843
[SCOFFS]

468
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:49,598
You dropped this at Russo's.

469
00:30:50,432 --> 00:30:52,768
You're smarter
than I gave you credit for, Nicky.

470
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:55,854
-You're not.
-Hey!

471
00:30:58,065 --> 00:31:01,151
You're a businessman, right?
So let's talk business.

472
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:03,695
I can offer you a lot of money
if you let us go.

473
00:31:03,904 --> 00:31:08,158
This isn't about money, Richie Rich.
This is about loyalty.

474
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:10,619
HELENA: He's got nothing to do
with any of this.

475
00:31:10,827 --> 00:31:16,083
SALVATI: Then what the hell is it about?
-My father had Michael murdered.

476
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:18,210
[SALVATI CHUCKLES]

477
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:23,423
Of course he did.
He didn't want you to know the truth.

478
00:31:23,632 --> 00:31:27,594
Your rat of a fiancé
was gathering evidence.

479
00:31:27,803 --> 00:31:30,347
He was talking to the frigging FBI.

480
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:34,101
The love of your life
was going to destroy your father.

481
00:31:34,309 --> 00:31:35,477
You're wrong.

482
00:31:35,685 --> 00:31:37,145
[GRUNTS]

483
00:31:38,021 --> 00:31:40,690
We found a laptop in Michael's bag,
Helena.

484
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:44,236
Everything that could send your father
and me to prison...

485
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:46,405
...for the rest of our lives was on it.

486
00:31:46,613 --> 00:31:49,199
-That computer...
-Was mine.

487
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:55,122
Michael wasn't the one
talking to the FBI. I was.

488
00:31:56,373 --> 00:31:59,876
-You?
-My father is a monster...

489
00:32:00,085 --> 00:32:03,130
...who doesn't care who he hurts
to keep his money and power.

490
00:32:03,338 --> 00:32:04,923
And I wanted it to stop.

491
00:32:05,132 --> 00:32:07,592
SALVATI: Well, then it's your fault
Michael's dead.

492
00:32:07,801 --> 00:32:11,721
Not your father for ordering the hit
or me for carrying it out.

493
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:15,475
Yours.

494
00:32:16,351 --> 00:32:19,146
You shot Michael?

495
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:25,527
In the chest. So he knew it was me.

496
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:31,032
Just like this.

497
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,246
[ALL GRUNTING AND GROANING]

498
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:04,191
You're gonna burn in hell.

499
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:06,401
It'll be worth it.

500
00:33:10,947 --> 00:33:11,990
[PANTING]

501
00:33:12,199 --> 00:33:13,241
Helena?

502
00:33:14,868 --> 00:33:16,369
[PANTING]

503
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:18,955
I didn't have a choice, Oliver.

504
00:33:20,332 --> 00:33:22,667
No one can know my secret.

505
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:30,175
CSU didn't find any usable prints
except for the three victims'.

506
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:32,093
One of them had a GSW to the chest.

507
00:33:32,302 --> 00:33:35,597
So who broke the necks
of Salvati and his buddy?

508
00:33:35,805 --> 00:33:39,100
Look, it's been a while
since the hood broke anyone's neck.

509
00:33:39,309 --> 00:33:41,269
And I didn't see any arrows
laying around.

510
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:44,981
Well, better pray that Frank Bertinelli
blames the hood for this.

511
00:33:45,190 --> 00:33:47,359
Because if he thinks it's the Triad...

512
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:49,986
...Starling City is ground zero
to World War III.

513
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:51,821
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

514
00:33:57,577 --> 00:33:59,037
You okay?

515
00:34:00,205 --> 00:34:04,209
-Spoke to my dad today.
-I bet that was fun.

516
00:34:04,417 --> 00:34:07,712
He explained to me what happened
with my credit card yesterday.

517
00:34:07,921 --> 00:34:10,257
And my checking account,
my savings account...

518
00:34:10,465 --> 00:34:14,469
...my brokerage account,
my stock portfolio.

519
00:34:15,428 --> 00:34:18,974
He cut me off completely.

520
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:22,143
What?

521
00:34:22,644 --> 00:34:24,688
My car got repossessed. That was fun.

522
00:34:24,896 --> 00:34:28,483
And I have to move out of my apartment
by the end of the month.

523
00:34:31,736 --> 00:34:34,239
You are gonna be fine, Tommy.

524
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:35,490
[SCOFFS]

525
00:34:35,699 --> 00:34:38,201
In fact, you are gonna be great.

526
00:34:39,494 --> 00:34:41,746
Merlyn money or not.

527
00:34:44,499 --> 00:34:46,626
And, you know...

528
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:51,631
...I have a mushroom
and olive Mario pizza...

529
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:55,010
...in my refrigerator
waiting to be eaten.

530
00:34:56,428 --> 00:35:00,640
-I suppose it's already paid for, right?
-Exactly.

531
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:19,868
-When did you get back?
-Just now.

532
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:21,578
[SIGHS]

533
00:35:27,917 --> 00:35:31,338
-I'm so happy to see you.
-Hmm.

534
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:35,425
But did you come home only
because you heard I was hurt?

535
00:35:36,092 --> 00:35:37,594
No.

536
00:35:37,802 --> 00:35:39,763
I was already on my way
when Thea called.

537
00:35:40,430 --> 00:35:44,851
I actually came home
because I missed my wife.

538
00:35:52,192 --> 00:35:53,318
MOIRA:
It's okay.

539
00:35:55,403 --> 00:35:57,906
-Is she all right?
-Walter's home.

540
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:00,283
She's gonna be fine.

541
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:04,079
Look, I'm sorry if I was a bitch
with you earlier.

542
00:36:04,996 --> 00:36:06,081
There were a few times.

543
00:36:06,289 --> 00:36:08,333
-Could you be more specific?
-Don't push it.

544
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:11,294
Don't worry. You weren't a bitch.

545
00:36:11,795 --> 00:36:14,172
At the hospital, you were a little...
A little bit.

546
00:36:14,381 --> 00:36:15,507
[CHUCKLES]

547
00:36:15,715 --> 00:36:19,511
Look, I'm just worried about you.

548
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:25,016
You seem really lonely.
And we all have our secrets, Ollie.

549
00:36:25,225 --> 00:36:27,852
Clearly you have yours.

550
00:36:28,603 --> 00:36:32,691
And it's fine
if you don't wanna share them with us.

551
00:36:33,108 --> 00:36:36,528
But I just really think you should
share them with someone.

552
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:58,133
I'd ask how you got in here...

553
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,261
...but the Starling City vigilante
comes and goes...

554
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:03,346
...as he pleases, doesn't he?

555
00:37:05,098 --> 00:37:06,850
How'd you know?

556
00:37:10,478 --> 00:37:12,188
I saw you fight.

557
00:37:15,108 --> 00:37:17,402
And I saw your eyes.

558
00:37:18,319 --> 00:37:21,948
That island changed you in ways that
only someone like me could understand.

559
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:23,658
No.

560
00:37:23,992 --> 00:37:25,452
What you're doing right now...

561
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:28,830
...I know that it feels like justice,
but it's not.

562
00:37:29,456 --> 00:37:35,253
-It's revenge.
-Sometimes revenge is justice.

563
00:37:38,006 --> 00:37:42,510
-Your father killed your fiancé.
-And what did your father do to you?

564
00:37:44,345 --> 00:37:48,808
Isn't the man in the hood
fighting to set things right?

565
00:37:49,017 --> 00:37:51,436
Why is your vendetta more valid
than mine?

566
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:54,189
We're the same, you and I.

567
00:37:54,939 --> 00:37:57,150
-No, we're not.
-Heh.

568
00:37:57,484 --> 00:37:59,194
Hiding in plain sight.

569
00:38:00,028 --> 00:38:04,991
Concealing our anger
with smiles and lies.

570
00:38:06,159 --> 00:38:08,286
Don't lie to me, Oliver.

571
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:11,706
You feel the same as I do. I know it.

572
00:38:11,915 --> 00:38:13,208
Why are you crying?

573
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:18,922
I don't know.

574
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:25,678
Maybe it's because I have been alone
in my hate for so long.

575
00:38:26,805 --> 00:38:29,432
-It feels...
-So good to tell the truth.

